00:00:40.648 --> 00:00:42.798
Concrete is a combination of coarse stone

00:00:42.798 --> 00:00:45.146
and sand particles, called aggregates,

00:00:45.146 --> 00:00:47.576
that mix with cement, a powdered blend

00:00:47.576 --> 00:00:49.236
of clay and limestone.

00:00:49.245 --> 00:00:51.185
When water gets added to this mix,

00:00:51.185 --> 00:00:52.815
the cement forms a paste and

00:00:52.815 --> 00:00:55.045
coats the aggregates, quickly hardening

00:00:55.045 --> 00:00:56.275
through a chemical reaction

00:00:56.275 --> 00:00:58.075
called hydration.

